cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR

This paper is about personalized product search, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel attention mechanism, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the interactions between queries and user purchase histories, which could fall under the categories of natural language processing (NLP) (cs.CL) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves large-scale experiments with search logs from a commercial e-commerce search engine, which could be considered a form of data science (cs.CY).
